&lt;Nelson Holdings International Ltd> saidit plans to expand the marketing of its video vending machines,which have been tested successfully in Toronto.    The machines, which can contain up to 400 videocassettes,have been placed in convenience stores and gas stations for thepast nine months.    Nelson said it now has machines in about 50 locations inToronto and will expand its sales effort across Canada thisyear.    The vending machines allow customers to rent avideocassette, using a credit card, and return the cassette tothe same machine. Reuter&#3;